request.description:
Required permission: `payroll.salary.view`.

Query params:
- employee_id nullable integer
- effective_on nullable date
- per_page nullable integer 1..100

Success response example:
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "employee_id": 10,
      "employee": {
        "id": 10,
        "employee_code": "EMP001",
        "full_name": "Dara Lim"
      },
      "amount": "725.50",
      "effective_date": "2026-04-01",
      "end_date": null,
      "is_current": true
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "total": 1
  }
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "effective_on": [
      "The effective on is not a valid date."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.salary.manage`.

Request body:
- employee_id required integer
- amount required numeric > 0
- effective_date required date
- end_date nullable date >= effective_date

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "employee_id": 10,
  "amount": "725.50",
  "effective_date": "2026-04-01",
  "end_date": null,
  "is_current": true
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "effective_date": [
      "The salary period overlaps an existing salary record for this employee."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.salary.manage`.

Request body:
- amount optional numeric > 0
- effective_date optional date
- end_date optional nullable date >= effective_date
- employee_id is prohibited

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "employee_id": 10,
  "amount": "680.00",
  "effective_date": "2026-04-01",
  "end_date": null,
  "is_current": true
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "amount": [
      "The amount field must be greater than 0."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.generate`.

Request body:
- month required YYYY-MM

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "payroll_month": "2026-04-01",
  "status": "draft",
  "employee_count": 1,
  "total_net_salary": "2100.00"
}

Validation error example (duplicate month):
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "month": [
      "A payroll run already exists for the selected month."
    ]
  }
}

All-or-nothing salary failure example:
{
  "message": "Payroll generation failed because some employees have no valid salary.",
  "errors": [
    {
      "employee_id": 11,
      "employee_code": "EMP002",
      "employee_name": "Sok Chan",
      "reason": "No valid salary found for selected month."
    }
  ]
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.view`.

Query params:
- month nullable YYYY-MM
- status nullable draft|approved|paid|cancelled
- per_page nullable integer 1..100

Success response example:
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "payroll_month": "2026-04-01",
      "status": "draft",
      "employee_count": 2,
      "total_net_salary": "4170.00"
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "total": 1
  }
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "The selected status is invalid."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.approve`.

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "status": "approved"
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "Only draft payroll runs can be approved."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.mark-paid`.

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "status": "paid"
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "Only approved payroll runs can be marked as paid."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.cancel`.

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "status": "cancelled"
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "Only draft or approved payroll runs can be cancelled."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.run.generate`.

Behavior:
- only draft payroll runs can regenerate
- existing payroll_items are deleted
- the month is recomputed inside a transaction

Success response example:
{
  "id": 1,
  "status": "draft",
  "total_base_salary": "2100.00",
  "total_net_salary": "2100.00"
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "Only draft payroll runs can be regenerated."
    ]
  }
}

Blocking salary failure example:
{
  "message": "Payroll generation failed because some employees have no valid salary.",
  "errors": [
    {
      "employee_id": 11,
      "employee_code": "EMP002",
      "employee_name": "Sok Chan",
      "reason": "No valid salary found for selected month."
    }
  ]
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}

Required permission: `payroll.payslip.view-own`.

Access rule:
- always scoped to the authenticated user's employee profile
- request employee_id is never trusted

Success response example:
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "payroll_run_id": 3,
      "payroll_month": "2026-04-01",
      "payroll_status": "paid",
      "base_salary": "2100.00",
      "overtime_pay": "30.00",
      "unpaid_leave_deduction": "50.00",
      "net_salary": "2080.00"
    }
  ],
  "meta": {
    "total": 1
  }
}

Validation error example:
{
  "message": "The given data was invalid.",
  "errors": {
    "status": [
      "The selected status is invalid."
    ]
  }
}

Auth or permission error example:
{
  "message": "Forbidden."
}
